abort outcome.","test_description":"Run report generation with two fake sources returning data and one fake source raising an availability exception. Assert process completes, report contains `data unavailable` for only the failed section, and other sections are still present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: behavior explicitly targets summary accuracy/faithfulness, which depends on real model output quality and can vary run-to-run; deterministic stubs would hide this failure. MOCK-HIDE: a mocked summarizer always passes expected phrasing and cannot reveal hallucination/omission errors. MULTI-STEP: this is one model decision stage, not a multi-agent chain. Rejection gate: Integration is rejected because behavior text requires \"accurately represents\" content quality, which a stub cannot validate.","test_description":"Use real summary-generation model calls on a fixed dataset with known key values. Evaluate output for factual inclusion/consistency of required metrics (e.g., exact counts, trend direction, critical incidents) across repeated runs with acceptance thresholds for faithfulness.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: this behavior boundary includes real external APIs and actual email transport/inbox delivery; in-process fakes can miss auth, TLS, SMTP/API acceptance, routing, and inbox placement issues. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail clients would pass while real delivery fails. LLM-DEP: although summary generation exists in the pipeline, this behavior's correctness criterion is inbox delivery, not model output quality. MULTI-STEP agentic correctness is not the assertion target. Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow are rejected because behavior text focuses on \"reaches ... inbox correctly,\" not on evaluating LLM decision quality.","test_description":"Execute the script in an environment hitting real source endpoints (or staging equivalents) and the real email delivery service to a test mailbox. Assert one end-to-end run produces an email in the configured recipient inbox with expected subject/body structure and attachments/sections present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is orchestration/state handoff across modules (send failure -> local persistence -> next-run retry). Integration with real local filesystem and controlled mail-client failure can expose real defects. REAL-INFRA brake: no mandatory real network outage or external scheduler is required; two invoked runs plus persisted state are enough to validate behavior. LLM-DEP: correctness is retry/persistence flow, not model output quality. Rejection gate: System is rejected because behavior text does not require proving real provider/network semantics, only fallback save and retry logic across runs.","test_description":"Run 1: configure mail client test double to fail with unreachable error; assert report file is written to configured local path and marked pending. Run 2: configure mail client to succeed; assert pending report is retried/sent and local backlog state is cleared or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,